EXTRACTED VALUE: Not a bad game in and of itself, but there's just not enough content here to make it seem worth the money you paid for it.
The Xbox 360 version of Kane's Wrath really shines through its slick interface.
It’s a game built with focus and one that’s going in a truly worthwhile direction, but that falls short of greatness. [Apr 2006, p.7]
So in the end, Call of Juarez isn’t a title worth much more than a rental.
Offers fast, sleek-looking gameplay, as graphics are impressive in almost all regards.
The fact that it is built upon completely ordinary tasks may seem pointless, but it's all the more believable for it.
